  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>Feast on a lovely varied buffet breakfast. Traditional tasty three course meals follow in the evening. You'll experience a Valtellina influence on classic Italian dishes with a wealth of flavour. Some say on Tripadvisor it's the best Italian they have had. If you have any dietary requirements just advise us when you book. </p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>1</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>You're really made to feel part of the family at the Hotel Lanz, they'll do all they can for you to ensure you have a great stay. The hotel is set in a chilled and tranquil location away from the lively <a data-udi="umb://document/e469a37cba1c498e9197c6963def7b89" href="/{localLink:umb://document/e469a37cba1c498e9197c6963def7b89}" title="Livigno">Livigno</a> streets but with easy access using the free resorts bus if you wish to nip into town for a coffee, bite to eat or experience the après on offer. The nearest ski-lift is 100 metres away and centre of town is 300 metres away, so everything isn't too far out of reach at all.</p>
<p>Recently renovated, the family run hotel has a comfortable and relaxed feel to it, none more so than in the spa. Turn up the heat in the sauna, cleanse the body in the Turkish bath or you can pay locally and enjoy the bubbles of the hot tub. </p>
<p>The restaurant has a lovely feel to it, wooden rafters overhead, decorative lighting hanging down and of course the large windows looking out over Livigno, the perfect setting to enjoy some wonderful Italian food, with a local Valtellina influence. The restaurant team will be able to help select a nice bottle of wine to accompany your meal and help bring out the wonderful flavours.</p>
<p> </p>
